description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you help us deliver our services during Covid-19?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people with a “Can do Attitude” to come and join our bank Hospital Support team at the Diana Princess of Wales Hospital in Grimsby who can work on positive Covid-19 areas. You will receive full training for the role of a Hospital Support Assistant (HSa) and FIT training in the use of personal protective equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of a HSa can be demanding, and requires flexibility to support us during periods of operational pressures; this includes day and night shifts as we provide a 24 hour service. You will work on a rota conducting cleaning on wards and public areas on week one and undertake catering duties delivery drinks and meals to our patient’s week two. So if you believe you have the physical agility to conduct ward cleans, and can demonstrate our values, &lt;strong&gt;Kindness, Courage and Respect&lt;/strong&gt; we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to be selected for an online interview you must provide&lt;/strong&gt; the following information in your application:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Details of any qualifications with the pass level indicated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any experience you have of working in either a cleaning or catering role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any experience of customer services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The reasons for any gaps in your working history&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Details of your referees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst the post is a Bank position (Zero hours contract) once you have completed your training and following a period of integration within the hospital environment you will have the opportunity to apply for any contracted posts within the department that may come available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once appointed you will access the many benefits of working for the NHS including an excellent pension scheme, increasing annual leave allowance of up to 41 days per annum (including bank holidays) once you have completed 10 years’ service, multiple discount schemes and the opportunity to develop and grow your skills within the NHS through our excellent training and development schemes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply and we will close the advert once we receive sufficient applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Mooney, HSA Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 03033 304348&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teresa Manship, HSA Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 03033 304348&lt;/p&gt;
